column5: Awesome fishing man !!!! Cheers some brute buckets for sure !!!!!
Thats some nice waters there. Nice buckets.  Almost looks like spots Justin Hoffman fishes out that way.
It doesn't get any better than flipping grass and trees!
Wow nice work!  Flipping and pitching is definitely something I need to improve on and try more often.
Sweet bunch of fish dude, well done!  But no houses? You might need to schedule an appointment with the eye doctor.   (don't mean anything by it, sometimes I just can't help myself.  )
Nice haul!  I especially like the boat mods you have made to the aluminum. Any more pics of those?  What you are happy with and what you would change or do different?  Cheers, Mark
Nice catch...  I've always wanted to try flipping for big largies
Is the standing deck in your tinner removable? This has me thinking.....
Nice catch. Those are some good looking piggies. What di you use for flipping.
